Requirements¶

  • implement a very simple sentiment analysis model to predict the sentiment score (column label)

  • Show the precision and recall of your model.

Preparing data for the machine learning algorithm¶

Here are some considerations about preparing data for the ML Algorithm¶
  • All the features are numeric except for "topic" and "text"
  • I will use a count vectorizer for transforming the "text" column into numbers and then into a DataFrame
  • In a similar way, will use LabelEncoder to transfrom "topic" column into numbers (encoding)
  • Finally, I will put everything together in a single dataframe. From this dataframe I extract X and y.
  • Moreover I will prepare training set and test set
  • Given that features are in a different numeric scale (for example "doc_pred" is between 0 and 1 while the feature "tokens" is between 7 and 22) .I will scale the training set and testing set separately in order to avoid data leakage

The Machine Learning Model¶

Some considerations about the machine learning model that I could use for this multiclass classification problem.¶

  • There are different classification algorithms that can be used for such a problem for example KNN, RandomForest or NaiveBayes
  • They all have their advantages and disadvantages when it comes to computational times, performance etc..
  • For this problem I will use a KNN which is a simple algorithm. Probably NaiveBayes or RandomForest are more appropriate for this problem and if time will allow me I will provide some implementations of those algorithms as well.
